item.title: Sericornis frontalis
item.dc:creator: david_francis
item.description: Juvenile or female. The bird was so tame/inquisitive I could use my close-up lens! Note the pale grey eye colour of this individual. The eyes are more often pale yellow, I think.

item.title: Callocephalon fimbriatum
item.dc:creator: david_francis
item.description: One of a noisy flock of 10 Gang-gang Cockatoos feeding on grubs in an Acacia mearnsii. They all looked to be young males with developing red head-feathering. They were quite unfazed by my close presence.

item.title: Threskiornis molucca
item.dc:creator: david_francis
item.description: Occasionally a fearless lone white ibis wanders around our backyard.

item.title: Dacelo novaeguineae
item.dc:creator: lydia
item.description: Sitting on the window-sill watching its reflection. It let me get VERY close and stayed there for around 5 minutes then flew off. Very beautiful.

item.title: Lichenostomus chrysops
item.dc:creator: david_francis
item.description: Feeding on cultivated Eucalyptus crenulata. Blue eyes.

item.title: Melithreptus lunatus
item.dc:creator: david_francis
item.description: Comparison of adult and immature White-naped Honeyeater. The immature bird has a brown head and the eye crescent and base of bill are both orange.

item.title: Oriolus sagittatus
item.dc:creator: david_francis
item.description: We have been seeing this bird feeding on the small grapes on the vine on our verandah. It takes fright easily but the shape, size and black-streaks on the white belly give a positive identification. It flies off quickly with the slightest disturbance before a photo can be taken.
